Structs/DialogNodeNextStep/Behavior.html.name: Behavior
Structs/DialogNodeNextStep/Behavior.html.abstract: What happens after the dialog node completes. The valid values depend on the node type: - The following values are valid for any node: - get_user_input - skip_user_input - jump_to - If the node is of type event_handler and its parent node is of type slot or frame, additional values are also valid: - if event_name=filled and the type of the parent node is slot: - reprompt - skip_all_slots - if event_name=nomatch and the type of the parent node is slot: - reprompt - skip_slot - skip_all_slots - if event_name=generic and the type of the parent node is frame: - reprompt - skip_slot - skip_all_slots If you specify jump_to, then you must also specify a value for the dialog_node property.

Structs/DialogNodeNextStep/Selector.html.name: Selector
